OL,6,FMeti was also charged and pleaded
OL,7,Fguilty to two other offences -
OL,8,Fpossession of a knife or bladed
OL,9,Farticle in a public place, and using a
OL,10,Fmotor vehicle without third party
OL,11,Finsurance.
OL,13,FBoth men pleaded guilty on Friday 22
OL,14,FNovember 2024 and were remanded into
OL,15,Fcustody until they were sentenced on
OL,16,FTuesday 4 February at Bristol Crown
OL,17,FCourt.
